'''A True, True Friend''' is the fourth of the seven [[songs]] featured in the season three finale, [[Magical Mystery Cure]]. The song was leaked during the week leading up to the [[Friendship is Magic animated media|episode]]'s airing on February 11, 2013. The last verse of the song is heard in the end [[credits]] for this episode. The song has been released as a sing-a-long on the [[Home media#Region 1|DVD]] ''My Little Pony Friendship is Magic: Princess Twilight Sparkle''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kidscartoons.about.com/od/dvd/fr/My-Little-Pony-Friendship-Is-Magic-Princess-Twilight-Sparkle-On-Dvd.htm|author=Tori Michel|title=My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic - Princess Twilight Sparkle on DVD|work=About.com|date=2013-04-16|accessdate=2013-04-19}}</ref> After the episode aired, Hasbro's ''My Little Pony'' Facebook page posted a recap-type video that used an alternate mix of the song, with clips from other parts of the episode.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.facebook.com/photo.php?v=10100116170036359|title=Feb 16, 2013 9:02am|work=Facebook|date=2013-02-16|accessdate=2013-02-17}}</ref>

This song serves as the sixth track on the album [[Songs of Ponyville]]. In the album version of the song, [[Rarity]]'s line "Lose the apple farm?", etc. has been re-recorded. In the soundtrack album [[Songs of Harmony]], the song is featured in an [[True True Friend Winter Wrap-Up|ultimate mash-up]] with the season one song [[Winter Wrap Up (song)|Winter Wrap Up]], including vocals by brony musician [[w:c:mlpfanart:BlackGryph0n|Gabriel Brown]]. It also serves as the third track on the [[My Little Pony 2015 Convention Collection]].

The instrumental version of this song can be heard on the levels menu for ''[[My Little Pony: Puzzle Party]]''. It is also used as background music for the last three eighths of the recap video of ''[[My Little Pony Friendship is Magic]]'' seasons one through six, [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zMrefXRfKYE "Days of Ponies Past"].
